SUMMARY:Deadline: Cultuurloket DigitALL: Implementation Contribution (Imple
 mentatiebijdrage\, 2026)
DESCRIPTION:A one-off 2026 call letting Dutch cultural institutions reuse a
 nd adapt digital technology that other institutions have already built and
  published in the open DigitALL Toolkit\, for example translation software
  shared between theatres or a streaming platform adapted for a new venue. 
 Grants run up to EUR 30\,000 and cover technical modification\, integratio
 n\, production and deployment costs. Eligible applicants are museums\, the
 atres\, music venues\, festivals\, film theatres and professional performi
 ng arts producers. Applications are submitted online and assessed in order
  of receipt rather than comparatively\, with a decision within ten weeks. 
 The deadline was extended from 31 May 2026 to 1 November 2026 after high d
 emand. IMPORTANT RESTRICTION: this route cannot be used to further develop
  your own pilot internally\; it exists specifically to spread another inst
 itution's working technology across the sector. For developing something n
 ew\, use the DigitALL pilot contribution instead.\n\nOrganisation: Cultuur
 loket DigitALL\nLocation: Netherlands and the Caribbean parts of the Kingd
 om. No city or region restriction.\nAward: Up to EUR 30\,000. Covers techn
 ical modification\, system integration\, production and deployment costs. 
 Hardware purchase alone is ineligible unless clearly essential to the publ
 ic experience. No stated co-financing percentage. No application fee.\nDur
 ation: Not specified\; scoped to a single implementation.\n\nMore: https:/
 /cultuurloketdigitall.nl/implementatiebijdrage/?utm_source=artificialnouve
 augrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://cultuurloketdigitall.nl/implementatiebijdrage/?utm_source=artif
 icialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Netherlands and the Caribbean parts of the Kingdom. No city or reg
 ion restriction.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mit-rd-samenwerking-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T062750Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260915
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260916
SUMMARY:Deadline: MIT R&D Collaboration Projects 2026 (MKB Innovatiestimule
 ring Topsectoren)
DESCRIPTION:The MIT R&D Collaboration Projects scheme (MIT R&D-samenwerking
 sprojecten\, part of MKB Innovatiestimulering Topsectoren) funds joint R&D
  projects by Dutch SMEs within the national Top Sectors and Mission-driven
  Innovation policy. The grant covers 35 percent of eligible costs: small p
 rojects of EUR 50\,000-200\,000 and large projects of EUR 200\,000-350\,00
 0 (with per-participant ranges of EUR 25\,000-100\,000 for small and EUR 2
 5\,000-175\,000 for large). Eligible applicants are consortia of at least 
 two collaborating SMEs\, with no single participant carrying more than 70 
 percent of costs. The national RVO round runs 9 June to 15 September 2026 
 (closes 17:00) and is a ranked tender\, not first-come-first-served\; some
  provinces run separate regional MIT windows. No application fee. Apply vi
 a RVO.\n\nOrganisation: Rijksdienst voor Ondernemend Nederland (RVO)\nLoca
 tion: Netherlands. SME consortia (minimum two collaborating SMEs).\nAward:
  Grant covering 35 percent of eligible costs. Small projects EUR 50\,000-2
 00\,000\; large projects EUR 200\,000-350\,000 per project (EUR 25\,000-10
 0\,000 or EUR 25\,000-175\,000 per participant). No application fee.\nDura
 tion: Project-based\; ranked tender (not first-come).\n\nMore: https://www
 .rvo.nl/subsidies-financiering/mit/rd-samenwerkingsprojecten?utm_source=ar
 tificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.rvo.nl/subsidies-financiering/mit/rd-samenwerkingsprojecten
 ?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Netherlands. SME consortia (minimum two collaborating SMEs).
END:VEVENT
